William A. WEBSTER v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE. No. 7275. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Nov. 13, 1936. F. E. Hagler, of Memphis, Tenn., for petitioner. Robert H. Jackson, Sewall Key, and Herman Oliphant, all of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel, it is ordered that the appeal herein be, and the same is, dismissed.
